explanation: The solution uses a StringBuilder to efficiently remove occurrences of the substring part from the string s. It iteratively finds and removes the leftmost occurrence of part until no more occurrences exist. The indexOf method is used to find the next occurrence, and the delete method is used to remove it. The time complexity is O(n*m) due to the indexOf and delete operations, where n is the length of s and m is the length of part. The space complexity is O(n) for storing the StringBuilder. 
